article.headline: Robert Morris 64, Fairleigh Dickinson 59
article.story: HACKENSACK, N.J. (AP) -- Tony Lee scored 19 points -- including two key free throws in the closing seconds -- as Robert Morris rallied for a 64-59 win over Fairleigh Dickinson on Thursday night. Jeremy Chappell added 14 points and five rebounds for the Colonials (12-5, 2-1 Northeast Conference), including two free throws that put his team ahead for good with three minutes left to play. Manny Ubilla scored 17 points to lead the Knights (5-8, 1-2), while Bernell Murray had 16 points, seven rebounds, four assists and four steals. Ubilla's 3-pointer with 4:19 remaining gave the Knights a 59-56 lead, but they wouldn't score again. Lee then hit a jumper to cut the lead to 59-58, and the Colonials would eventually seal the win by going 6-for-7 from the free throw line over the final three minutes. Fairleigh Dickinson narrowly won the battle of the boards 34-33, but the Knights were hurt by their own sloppy play, committing 22 turnovers.
